race.comment: POBLANO (5) was simply dominant a fortnight ago at Pinjarra where he led and ran away for an impressive victory. Pike was on board there and he rides the mare again today. The form out of that race has already been franked and with further improvement expected, she'll be tough to hold out once more. MONTE TREMEZZO (1) comes here third-up and with some strong performances in tougher company under her belt. She's out to 1200m now which is the query, though Cooper's claim comes in handy and she's drawn nicely. Can get an economical run and bounce back to winning ways. THE NUN (6) missed in a photo at Pinjarra 24 days ago. Ticks a few boxes again today. OFFSHORE (4) is better than she showed last start and can bounce back.
